@devel-bobm
One simple solution for this is to add this to the Meter interface:
/**
 * Returns the number of integer digits this meter recommends for the display.
 *
 * @returns the number of integer digits, or 0 if no recommendation is given
 */
public default int getRecommendedIntegerDigits() {
    return 0;
}

/**
 * Returns the number of decimal digits this meter recommends for the display.
 *
 * @returns the number of decimal digits, or 0 if no recommendation is given
 */
public default int getRecommendedDecimalDigits() {
    return 0;
}

The MeterFrame would when check Meter.getRecommendedIntegerDigits() to check if it's value is non zero and if so, use it. The LnPredefinedMeters would then override these methods to return the desired number of digits. This would not break any of the other meters so it would be safe to add.
